Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While the kettle boils, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks)
and discard the core and seeds.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams}, chopped pepper and
onion to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and the veg has softened,
~{8-10%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{}
with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @lime{1}(cut into wedges) into wedges.

Once the chicken is golden and the veg has softened, add the garlic to the pan
and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @ketjap manis{25%grams}, @gochujang paste{50%grams},
@honey{15%grams}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @water for the sauce{75%milliliters}
into the chicken and veg.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Squeeze in some lime juice from a lime wedge. Taste and season with salt, pepper
and more lime juice if needed.

Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the sweet and sticky chicken stir-fry.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams} and serve with any
remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!